Hello Steve.

I wonder what state the miktex installation is in, because amsart
is a standard part of any LaTeX distribution, so it should be there
already. Can the user process documents of other document classes
like "article"?

The ams class files should be at <TEXMF>\tex\latex\amscls
where "<TEXMF>" means the root of the TeX files of your miktek
installation (article.cls should be at <TEXMF>\tex\latex\base).

>From that CTAN web page there is also amscls.tds.zip which should
unpack everything into the appropriate standard location.

You can see the installation instructions at
   ftp://ftp.ams.org/pub/tex/amslatex/install.txt
or
   http://mirror.ctan.org/ctan/macros/latex/required/amslatex/amscls/doc/install.txt
or inside the zip file you already downloaded.

